    "In contrast, heads in Layers 1 and 2 each yield smaller gains (typically ∆P < 0.20), with a more uniform distribution of influence and slightly weaker impact in Layer 2 than Layer 1, reinforcing the pattern of diminishing causal strength in deeper blocks.",
    "These results point to a sparse internal circuit, where only a handful of heads drive the bulk of the model's causal computation, guiding us to focus on these key heads for finer positional analyses.",
